{{Quote|My Marker. Good for any ship on my lot. Your choice of my stock.|[[Lando Calrissian/Legends|Lando Calrissian]] to [[Han Solo/Legends|Han Solo]]|<ref name="Rebel Dawn">''[[Rebel Dawn]]''</ref>}}
The '''Cloud City Sabacc Tournament''' was a [[Sabacc/Legends|sabacc]] competition held in [[Cloud City/Legends|Cloud City]], [[Bespin/Legends|Bespin]].

The circa [[17 BBY/Legends|17 BBY]] tournament was the site of a [[Battle of Bespin (Imperial Period)|confrontation]] between [[Darga Jiramma Mionne|Darga]] the [[Hutt/Legends|Hutt]], the [[Galactic Empire/Legends|Galactic Empire]], and the [[Alderaanian Resistance]].

In [[5 BBY/Legends|5 BBY]], [[Cix Trouvee]] lost the [[YT-1300 light freighter/Legends|YT-1300 light freighter]] [[Millennium Falcon/Legends|''Millennium Falcon'']] to [[Lando Calrissian/Legends|Lando Calrissian]] in this tournament. In [[2 BBY/Legends|2.5 BBY]], [[Han Solo/Legends|Han Solo]] won the tournament, defeating Calrissian in the final game and winning the ''Millennium Falcon''.

==Tournament rules==
The tournament was four days in duration, and attracted [[The galaxy/Legends|the galaxy's]] best players. The "buy-in" amount was 10,000 [[Galactic Credit Standard/Legends|credits]]. Each day, over half the competitors would be eliminated, until one table remained for the final game.

Usually the gaming hall itself was strictly for players only, while spectators could watch the games from the holo-projection lounge. There were exceptions however, such as a female [[Twi'lek/Legends|Twi'lek]] who was seen by Calrissian's side during the 2.5 BBY final.

==The Empire, Darga, and the Alderaanian Resistance, circa 17 BBY==
This particular tournament was held in the [[Royal Casino/Legends|Royal Casino]], attracting over fifty competitors. At the second day's conclusion, the remaining competitors were [[Lieutenant/Legends|Lieutenant]] [[Armen Arandis]], [[Creeska]], [[Silas Draver]], [[Lady/Legends|Lady]] [[Mirana Fioro]], [[Captain/Legends|Captain]] [[Koroma Moro]], [[Vorn Zaday]], [[Szygar]] and a member of the [[Alderaanian Resistance]].

Members of the Alderaanian Resistance infiltrated the event in order to track down Darga the [[Hutt/Legends|Hutt]] and learn more about the [[Sarlacc Project]]. The Resistance believed that Darga and Lt. Arandis were using the tournament as a cover-up to exchange funds in a clandestine deal involving [[Tibanna/Legends|tibanna]] and [[Slavery/Legends|slaves]]&mdash;all part of the Sarlacc Project. Toward the end of the tournament, Lt. Arandis lost all his winnings to Fioro in an unusual tactic. This move revealed to the Resistance that Fioro was Darga's agent in the transaction.

The finalists were Fioro, Moro, Zaday, and possibly the Alderaanian Resistance member, though the end of the tournament was marred by a violent awards ceremony. Competitor Silas Draver attempted to steal access codes of the bank account holding the total winnings, taking Fioro as a hostage. Draver's stunt was thwarted by the Alderaanian Resistance and security. Lt. Arandis was killed in the skirmish.

==Trouvee and Calrissian, 5 BBY==
In [[5 BBY/Legends|5 BBY]], [[Cix Trouvee]] joined a contest set up by a group of [[Hutt/Legends|Hutts]] to bet on the outcome of an impending [[Galactic Empire/Legends|Imperial]] attack on the [[Yag'Dhul insurgents]]. During [[Battle of Yag'Dhul (Imperial era)|the battle]], however, the Imperials discovered the gamblers, and, believing them to be supplying intelligence to the insurgents, attacked them. Trouvee fled with his copilot, [[Waglin]], in his [[Starship/Legends|starship]], the [[Millennium Falcon/Legends|''Millennium Falcon'']]. Before he could escape, however, the [[Imperial I-class Star Destroyer/Legends|''Imperial I''-class Star Destroyer]] [[Desolator (Imperial-class)/Legends|''Desolator'']] opened [[Laser/Legends|fire]] on him, missing and hitting two [[TIE/IN interceptor/Legends|TIE fighters]]. This pushed the starfighter count two higher than the count on which Trouvee had bet; Trouvee, in desperate need of [[Galactic Credit Standard/Legends|credits]], entered this tournament. He made it until the third day of the tournament, when the pot had grown to ninety-thousand credits and Trouvee had a hand he didn't think could be beat. By then he had been forced to throw in the ''Millennium Falcon'' and Calrissian beat Trouvee with an [[Idiot's Array/Legends|Idiot's Array]], winning the ''Falcon''.

==Solo vs Calrissian, 2.5 BBY==
Han Solo won this tournament, held in the [[Yarith Bespin/Legends|Yarith Bespin]] and consisting of over a hundred competitors. Five finalists qualified for the final game: a male [[Chadra-Fan/Legends|Chadra-Fan]], a male [[Bothan/Legends|Bothan]], a female [[Rodian/Legends|Rodian]], Lando Calrissian and Han Solo. A [[Unidentified Bith card dealer|Bith card dealer]] conducted the game.

Three and a half hours into the final game, the Bothan had "bombed out." Shortly after, the Rodian folded, and pulled out. At this point, the [[Sabacc pot/Legends|sabacc pot]] contained just under 20,000 credits. The Chadra-Fan folded early in the last hand, leaving only Calrissian and Solo to contend the title.

In addition to several thousand credits, Calrissian bet any one ship on his lot on [[Nar Shaddaa/Legends|Nar Shaddaa]]. Calrissian almost won the tournament, only being one card away from holding an Idiot's Array. His final hand included the Idiot, the Two of Staves and the Seven of Flasks. Solo won the tournament with the Queen of Air and Darkness, the Five of Coins, the Six of Staves, and the Master of Coins: [[Pure Sabacc/Legends|Pure Sabacc]].

Solo won the 20,000 credits in the sabacc pot, plus roughly the same amount again he had won throughout the four days. When Calrissian asked Solo to choose any ship on his lot, Han picked the ''Millennium Falcon'' without hesitation. Calrissian protested, stating that it was his personal ship and not part of the deal, but Solo insisted that it was technically "on his lot" and therefore a valid choice. Calrissian finally conceded, and the ''Falcon'' was now the property of Han Solo.

